   VENTURE: United Press International and Financial News
Network Inc. formed a joint venture to provide business and
financial news and data. Infotechnology Inc., which owns all
of UPI and 47% of FNN, named Jonathan Fram president of the
venture, UPI Financial Information Services. Mr. Fram is
president of Infotechnology's Institutional Research Network.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   WHO'S NEWS: Jeffrey Korchek was promoted to vice
president, business affairs, for MCA Inc.'s Universal
Pictures unit. He was a business affairs executive in
Universal's legal department. . . .Jack L. Farnsworth became
president of the higher education division of Simon &amp;
Schuster, a unit of Paramount Communications Co. He succeeds
Patrick Donaghy, who remains executive vice president. He was
senior vice president of North American operations for
Maxwell Communications Corp.'s Maxwell Macmillan
International.
